CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 8, 1960, pg. 16, reads: "'Doesn't Hurt' - Elston Howard, New York Yankees' catcher, tells Yogi Berra his injured catching finger is coming along fine.  Howard proved his point in the ninth inning Tuesday as he knocked a two-run, pinch-hit homer in a losing cause in the opening World Series game. - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: New York Yankees baseball players Elston Howard and Yogi Berra in front of dugout, at opening game of 1960 World Series, Forbes Field
